{"id":"345784645_Prospects_for_the_use_of_artificial_intelligence_systems_in_gastroenterology","abstract":"The lecture is devoted to a new direction in clinical medicine — the possibility of using artificial intelligence — the field of computer science, which is engaged in modeling the method of acquiring and using knowledge specific to humans. The basis for a correct diagnosis is a combination of experience, the ability to think and act non-standard in difficult cases. A powerful system of generalization and classification, implemented in intelligent systems, allows you to reduce a huge number of possible situations to a small number of typical situations by which decisions or hypotheses are formed.","authors":["Кобринский Борис Аркадьевич","Anatoly Khavkin","G. V. Volynets","Кобринский Аркадьевич Борис"],"meta":["September 2020Ėksperimental'nai͡a i klinicheskai͡a gastroėnterologii͡a = Experimental & clinical gastroenterology","DOI:10.31146/1682-8658-ecg-179-7-109-117"],"references":["344053223_The_point_system_evaluation_for_assessing_the_degree_of_disability_in_children_of_the_first_three_years_of_life","341146739_Modern_view_of_biliary_atresia_in_children","338850711_Violation_of_the_liver_structure_and_function_in_congenital_cholestatic_diseases_in_the_young","336283797_Application_of_Artificial_Intelligence_to_Gastroenterology_and_Hepatology","325851046_MEDICAL_DIAGNOSIS_ONTOLOGY_FOR_INTELLIGENT_DECISION_SUPPORT_SYSTEMS","333638335_SCLEROSING_CHOLANGITIS_IN_CHILDREN_AND_ADOLESCENTS_CURRENT_STATE_OF_THE_PROBLEM","330060080_Artificial_intelligence_and_computer-aided_diagnosis_in_colonoscopy_current_evidence_and_future_directions","324795387_Progressive_familial_intrahepatic_cholestasis_Clinical_picture_diagnosis_treatment","324701970_Differential_diagnostics_of_congenital_cholestatic_diseases_in_children_of_early_age","324040049_Establishment_of_comprehensive_prediction_model_of_acute_gastrointestinal_injury_classification_of_critically_ill_patients","321496042_